name: Hit Man movie
summary: Critical reviews of the Netflix movie "Hit Man" vary in their assessment. Forbes and Keith & the Movies find the film disappointing, while EL PAÍS USA calls it "nonsensical." Polygon praises a standout scene and the stealthy romantic comedy elements, while NPR highlights Glen Powell's performance. Vulture and Northwest Arkansas Democrat-Gazette commend Powell and Linklater's blend of screwball comedy and serious themes. Variety questions the potential theatrical success of the film, while Rough Draft Atlanta explores the relationship between truth and con in the movie. Men's Health delves into the true story inspiration and the current whereabouts of Gary Johnson, a real-life hitman who is a character in the film. Overall, the reviews indicate a range of opinions on "Hit Man," with some critics finding it less impressive than others.

name: William Anders
summary: Former Apollo 8 astronaut William Anders, known for capturing the iconic "Earthrise" photograph during the mission, has unfortunately passed away in a plane crash near the San Juan Islands in Washington. Anders was 90 years old at the time of his passing. The plane crash resulted in his tragic death. Anders played a significant role in the Apollo 8 mission, which achieved the first successful orbit around the moon in December 1968. He took the renowned "Earthrise" photograph, which depicted the Earth rising over the lunar horizon.
